SIMPLE: zulu
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zulu
<hw>Zu"lu</hw> <pr>(z⟦oomac⟧"l⟦oomac⟧)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[Also <ets>Zooloo</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Any member of the
tribe of Zulus; a Zulu-Kaffir. See <er>Zulus</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Philol.)</fld> <def>One of the most important
members of the South African, or Bantu, family of languages, spoken
partly in Natal and partly in Zululand, but understood, and more or less
in use, over a wide territory, at least as far north as the Zambezi; --
called also <altname>Zulu-Kaffir</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A word used in spoken communications to represent
the letter <it>Z</it>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zulu-Kaffir</ent>⟦br⟧
